📌 System Testing – GS-Level Understanding
1. Core Concept
System testing validates the entire application (all integrated components) in an environment that simulates production.
Focuses on:
Functional correctness
Performance under load
Security and compliance
End-to-end workflows
2. Types of System Testing
Type	Purpose	GS-Level Notes
Functional	Validate features against requirements	Use test cases covering all endpoints and user scenarios
Load / Performance	Stress test system under high traffic	Measure response times, resource usage
Security	Penetration tests, input validation	Critical for financial apps
Regression	Ensure new changes don’t break old functionality	Automated in CI/CD pipelines
End-to-End	Simulate real user journeys	Combines all microservices, DB, caches, and message queues
3. Best Practices
Automated test suites integrated with CI/CD
Test environment parity with production using containers
Mock external dependencies (3rd party APIs) for reliable tests
Test data management to avoid production corruption
Observability during tests to catch subtle issues
Python Example – System Test with FastAPI + Pytest
# main.py
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI()

@app.get("/health")
def health():
    return {"status": "healthy"}

@app.get("/trade/{user_id}")
def trade(user_id: int):
    if user_id <= 0:
        return {"error": "invalid user id"}
    return {"user_id": user_id, "status": "trade executed"}

# test_main.py
from fastapi.testclient import TestClient
from main import app

client = TestClient(app)

def test_health():
    resp = client.get("/health")
    assert resp.status_code == 200
    assert resp.json() == {"status": "healthy"}

def test_trade_valid():
    resp = client.get("/trade/123")
    assert resp.status_code == 200
    assert resp.json() == {"user_id": 123, "status": "trade executed"}

def test_trade_invalid():
    resp = client.get("/trade/-1")
    assert resp.status_code == 200
    assert "error" in resp.json()

GS-Level Notes:

Uses FastAPI TestClient for integration-style testing
Covers edge cases like invalid inputs
Can integrate with CI/CD for automated system tests
